oes, which summons the 6-cost Crimson Clergy with Taunt and Lifesteal. The opponent uses 'Lesser Heal,' restoring 2 health, and Crimson Clergy attacks JustSomeDude's hero for 1 damage. The opponent ends their turn, leaving JustSomeDude with 25 health after another minion attack. JustSomeDude's turn begins with 15 health, and he plays 'Spectral Cutlass,' followed by 'Dehydrate,' which deals 4 damage to the opponent’s 4/4 minion, destroying it and healing JustSomeDude for 4, reducing the opponent’s health to 19. He remarks, 'Well, that's a dead card.' Crimson Clergy asserts, 'You have no idea what I'm capable of.' JustSomeDude plays 'Lightshow,' dealing 2 damage to two enemy minions, destroying a 2/2 minion and reducing a 5/5 minion to 3/5, lamenting, 'No, my worm!' He mutters, 'Right, protocol,' and 'Oh, furnace fuel. I did forget about that.' He ends his turn with 15 health and the opponent at 19. In another instance, JustSomeDude comments, 'Oh, they're dead,' followed by 'Nice.' The opponent, Lololo, plays their 'Demon Claws' Hero Power, and JustSomeDude plays 'Kajamite Creation,' remarking, 'Good job, Tess.' An announcer declares, 'Garona versus Illidan! This ends now! We battle endlessly for glory!' JustSomeDude observes, 'Those don't look like my weapon,' as the opponent plays 'Instrument Tech,' summoning a 1/2 minion. After JustSomeDude ends his turn, his hand is updated to include 'Mic Drop,' and the strategic early-game phase continues with additional game sound effects and exclamations like 'Don't poop perfection' and 'Shining.'"
